## Redistribution Notes

When redistributing TermOS, you must comply with the licenses of all included components:

### GPL Requirements (Source Code Availability)

The following components require source code availability when distributing binaries:

1. **GPL v2 components**: Linux Kernel, eudev, NetworkManager, BlueZ, cryptsetup, btrfs-progs, e2fsprogs, ALSA utilities, git, polkit, util-linux, mpv, elinks, D-Bus
   - Sources available from respective upstream repositories (linked in tables above)
   - Linux kernel source: https://www.kernel.org/

2. **GPL v3 components**: greetd, tuigreet, cool-retro-term, GRUB
   - Source code must be made available
   - Sources available from respective upstream repositories

3. **Syslinux (GPL v2)**: x86_64 builds only
   - Source: https://wiki.syslinux.org/

### Permissive License Requirements

Components under MIT, Apache 2.0, BSD, and ISC licenses require:
- Retention of copyright and permission notices
- No additional redistribution restrictions
- Attribution as specified in original licenses

Key permissive components:
- **Apache 2.0**: Alpine Linux, alacritty
- **MIT**: term39, cage, wlroots, seatd, xwayland, mesa, libinput, foot, pipewire, wireplumber
- **BSD**: OpenRC, openssh-client, sof-firmware
- **ISC**: sudo

### Firmware Redistribution

**linux-firmware** contains mixed licenses:
- Many proprietary firmware binaries with redistribution permission
- Some components under GPL, BSD, or other open licenses
- See the `WHENCE` file in the linux-firmware repository for complete licensing details
- Redistributable but modification may be restricted for some firmware blobs

**CPU Microcode** (AMD, Intel):
- Redistributable under vendor-specific licenses
- Generally allows redistribution but not modification

## Full License Texts

Full license texts for each component can be found at:

- **Apache License 2.0**: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0
- **GNU GPL v2**: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.html
- **GNU GPL v3**: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html
- **MIT License**: See above or https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT
- **BSD 2-Clause**: https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-2-Clause
- **BSD 3-Clause**: https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause
- **ISC License**: https://opensource.org/licenses/ISC
- **Vim License**: https://github.com/vim/vim/blob/master/LICENSE

